<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
<taxonomicName authorityName="D. F. Xie &amp; X. J. He" authorityYear="2022" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Allium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Allium heterophyllum" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="heterophyllum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Allium heterophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. dumebuchum" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="dumebuchum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">A. dumebuchum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to its rhomboid scape in cross-section. However, it is clearly distinguished from 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. dumebuchum" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="dumebuchum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">A. dumebuchum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in perianth (white to light purple vs. light purple), leaves (not tortuous and not flesh vs. slight tortuous and flesh), the cross-section of leaves (two types vs. one type), 
<normalizedToken originalValue="flowers’">flowers'</normalizedToken>
density (loose inflorescence vs. many-flowered) (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Morphological characters of Allium heterophyllum A, D single flower with light purple or white color B, E outer (left) and inner (right) tepals C, F inner (top) and outer (bottom) tepals and stamen G stamen and trait at the base H ovary I cross-section of ovary showing the carpels J-L the cross-section of leaf showing the blade characters M cross-section of rhomboid scapes N seeds' characters." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.190.77449.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647499" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">2</figureCitation>
; Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 2" captionStartId="T2" captionText="Table 2. The diagnostic morphological characters of Allium heterophyllum and related species." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/F04ACB34CEB0D97AAD718F4379E9760B" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" tableUuid="F04ACB34CEB0D97AAD718F4379E9760B">2</tableCitation>
), flowering season (late August to September vs. late September to October), and karyotype (2n = 16 vs. 2n = 32) (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. The chromosome complement of Allium heterophyllum (2 n = 2 x = 16)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.190.77449.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/647501" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">4</figureCitation>
). Compared to other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fourreau" authorityYear="1869" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Rhizirideum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Rhizirideum" order="Asparagales" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Rhizirideum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (e.g., 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. scenescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="scenescens">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">A. scenescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. spirale" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="spirale">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">A. spirale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. spurium" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="spurium">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">A. spurium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. heterophyllum" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="heterophyllum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">A. heterophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also shows distinctive morphological characters, such as rhomboid scape in cross-section, unique two types of leaves, loose flowers, white to light purple color of perianth and filaments, and flowering season.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Table-UUID="F04ACB34CEB0D97AAD718F4379E9760B" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/F04ACB34CEB0D97AAD718F4379E9760B" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" start="Table 2" startId="T2">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Table 2.</emphasis>
